At Least 9 Killed, 24 Injured in Southwest China Bus Crash
At least nine people were killed and 24 injured after a bus carrying 37 passengers overturned in China’s southwest Yunnan province, Xinhua news agency reported on Sunday.
At least nine people were killed and 24 injured after a bus carrying 37 passengers overturned in China’s southwest Yunnan province, Xinhua news agency reported on Sunday.
The accident took place on Saturday night shortly before midnight on an expressway between Dali and Chuxiong cities.
All injured people, with some of them in grave condition, were taken to nearby hospitals. Police are trying to establish the cause of the accident.